<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="552" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/399a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-22T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 22,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>270. Department’s 262, November 11th, 7 P.M. You may present formula to
                            Diplomatic Body for consideration.</p>
                        <p>Repeat to Tokyo for its information as Department’s 144.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>